1
00:01:25,810 --> 00:01:34,850
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,840
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:45,440
Hello.

4
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,539
Zhuang Zhuang?

5
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:47,830
Yes, I am.

6
00:01:48,259 --> 00:01:49,450
I'm head of Design Team No. 2.

7
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:50,070
My name is Toby.

8
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:50,570
Nice to meet you.

9
00:01:50,570 --> 00:01:51,430
Care for a tour?

10
00:01:51,509 --> 00:01:52,009
Sure.

11
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:52,729
Let's go.

12
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,280
This is the conference area.

13
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,560
But we don't use it very often.

14
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,729
It's poorly designed,

15
00:01:57,729 --> 00:01:59,190
so Ms. Yue doesn't like it.

16
00:01:59,509 --> 00:02:01,370
Upstairs is the styling section.

17
00:02:01,430 --> 00:02:01,890
Here...

18
00:02:02,370 --> 00:02:03,770
is our main battlefield.

19
00:02:06,450 --> 00:02:07,430
This is the tailoring area,

20
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:08,080
where ready-to-wear

21
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:08,970
clothes are altered.

22
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:09,460
Our own factory

23
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:10,780
covers the massive production.

24
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:12,680
This area is for selecting fabrics.

25
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,880
This space is taken by Design Team No. 2.

26
00:02:15,060 --> 00:02:16,000
And that area is used

27
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,040
for accessory design.

28
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:18,010
This is my desk.

29
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,650
Yours is over there.

30
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:20,400
Got it.

31
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:21,740
As for this place,

32
00:02:21,740 --> 00:02:22,630
it is where we make reports

33
00:02:22,630 --> 00:02:23,500
to Ms. Yue.

34
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,770
Where is Ms. Yue?

35
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,170
I should go say hi to her.

36
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,920
The "tiger's den" is over there.

37
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:32,130
"Tiger"?

38
00:02:32,610 --> 00:02:34,340
The kind that eats human flesh.

39
00:02:34,530 --> 00:02:35,860
If she doesn't call for you,

40
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:37,990
I suggest you do not easily go meet her.

41
00:02:38,530 --> 00:02:39,630
Aren't I here to work

42
00:02:39,630 --> 00:02:40,630
as her assistant?

43
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,280
That's merely a title.

44
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,960
What matters is what you want to do here.

45
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,250
If you want to learn fashion design,

46
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:46,380
then spend more time

47
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,660
with Design Team No. 2.

48
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,280
If you want to learn styling,

49
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,280
then go upstairs.

50
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:51,430
What's your idea?

51
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:51,900
I...

52
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:53,690
I definitely want to learn

53
00:02:53,690 --> 00:02:54,930
as much as I can from you.

54
00:02:54,930 --> 00:02:56,500
I'll go on a bit more then.

55
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,079
Do you usually read?

56
00:02:58,079 --> 00:02:58,870
What kind of books?

57
00:02:58,870 --> 00:03:00,030
Any kind.

58
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:00,900
You can find

59
00:03:01,070 --> 00:03:01,930
the latest issues

60
00:03:01,930 --> 00:03:03,560
of all sorts of fashion magazines here.

61
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,080
But whether you understand
the content or not

62
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:05,870
is on you.

63
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,310
I have things to do.

64
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:08,520
Will you be okay on your own?

65
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,010
Yes.

66
00:03:09,090 --> 00:03:10,180
You are still on probation.

67
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:10,870
Do your best.

68
00:03:10,870 --> 00:03:11,410
Thanks.

69
00:03:19,290 --> 00:03:23,230
[Police Office]

70
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:26,370
Sit down.

71
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,290
I dare not.

72
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:30,410
Sit down.

73
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,780
What, are you scared?

74
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:35,079
I'm worried about being wronged!

75
00:03:35,079 --> 00:03:35,690
"Scared"?

76
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,160
You were caught red-handed.

77
00:03:38,620 --> 00:03:39,820
You can't be wronged.

78
00:03:40,090 --> 00:03:41,930
I was tricked by Li Xiaobo!

79
00:03:42,210 --> 00:03:43,000
He told me

80
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,710
he needed to buy tickets for his company,

81
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:46,630
but he couldn't stand
waiting in the queue anymore.

82
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:47,410
I figured

83
00:03:47,410 --> 00:03:48,150
I had been staying up

84
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:49,579
till dawn writing scripts

85
00:03:49,579 --> 00:03:51,040
with my mentor these days,

86
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:52,970
so I was available that late at night.

87
00:03:52,970 --> 00:03:54,440
He also promised

88
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:56,070
to pay me for the trouble.

89
00:03:56,579 --> 00:03:57,910
That's why I went for it.

90
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:00,650
When I picked you up
at the train station police office,

91
00:04:00,650 --> 00:04:02,510
I was told you're a screenwriter.

92
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:05,270
You do know how to make up stories.

93
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,840
Are you denying your involvement

94
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,180
to make yourself look innocent?

95
00:04:08,180 --> 00:04:09,020
I'm not making up a story!

96
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:10,550
Each and every word is true!

97
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,520
I've been in Beijing for a while.

98
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,060
Light has finally shed on my life.

99
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:15,720
Of course I'll run towards it.

100
00:04:16,010 --> 00:04:17,060
Why would I ruin that

101
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,860
with such a serious illegal act?

102
00:04:19,890 --> 00:04:21,180
Who can testify for you?

103
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:22,160
Li Xiaobo can!

104
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,840
He was caught too, wasn't he?

105
00:04:24,710 --> 00:04:25,300
Tang,

106
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:28,110
[Public Security Office]

107
00:04:25,930 --> 00:04:27,040
This time, thank you so much

108
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,250
for making Li Xiaobo tell the truth,

109
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:32,330
[Reception Room]

110
00:04:28,450 --> 00:04:30,240
so I could clear my name.

111
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:31,630
I know life is never easy

112
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:33,220
for dream chasers like you in Beijing.

113
00:04:33,220 --> 00:04:34,330
There is a lot to pay—

114
00:04:34,330 --> 00:04:35,860
life necessities and stuff.

115
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:37,330
As long as you hang in there
and work hard,

116
00:04:37,330 --> 00:04:39,190
things will keep getting better.

117
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:40,890
But if you take the wrong path

118
00:04:40,890 --> 00:04:41,920
and jeopardize yourself,

119
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,780
then your dream

120
00:04:43,010 --> 00:04:43,950
will remain just a dream.

121
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:47,180
[Archives]

122
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:44,690
Right.

123
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:46,670
Tang, rest assured.

124
00:04:46,810 --> 00:04:48,010
I'll definitely write

125
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,250
heroes like you

126
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,600
into my future scripts.

127
00:04:50,659 --> 00:04:51,790
Stop flattering me.

128
00:04:51,890 --> 00:04:53,659
You live within my jurisdiction,

129
00:04:53,659 --> 00:04:54,720
so I just did my job.

130
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:56,220
Go home to eat now.

131
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:58,370
Thank you!

132
00:04:59,180 --> 00:04:59,780
Off you go.

133
00:05:10,090 --> 00:05:11,060
My apologies.

134
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:11,630
I'm late.

135
00:05:11,630 --> 00:05:13,690
You won't be late for class, will you?

136
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:18,070
Freeze!

137
00:05:21,980 --> 00:05:22,910
I-I'll confess.

138
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:24,920
You're confessing even before I ask?

139
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,510
I'm just hoping for leniency

140
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:28,040
by showing a good attitude.

141
00:05:30,010 --> 00:05:31,140
Did I tell you to sit?

142
00:05:35,180 --> 00:05:35,920
Confess now.

143
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:36,640
Yes!

144
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:39,010
Well, Officer Zhuang,

145
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,500
I did do wrong.

146
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,080
I scalped tickets at the train station.

147
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:43,780
And then...

148
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,530
Wait. What were you thinking?

149
00:05:49,010 --> 00:05:49,630
How could you

150
00:05:49,630 --> 00:05:50,450
cause trouble again

151
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:52,310
after just a few days of learning?

152
00:05:52,330 --> 00:05:53,860
I wasn't finished yet.

153
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:54,830
I didn't really scalp tickets.

154
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:56,000
I was deceived.

155
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:57,870
I'm partly at fault, though,

156
00:05:57,870 --> 00:05:59,870
for trying to make some quick money.

157
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,180
You have food and a place to stay.

158
00:06:01,180 --> 00:06:03,040
Why are you so eager to make money?

159
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:10,930
Are you still thinking

160
00:06:10,930 --> 00:06:12,130
about my lesson fees?

161
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,000
N-No.

162
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,430
Stop eating.

163
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,840
I-I promise

164
00:06:22,870 --> 00:06:24,740
I won't do it again. I won't.

165
00:06:25,370 --> 00:06:27,230
Did you think I'd take your money?

166
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:30,580
Money you took risks to make?

167
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,890
We lost money in our business.

168
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:34,890
That was my fault.

169
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:37,370
I was the reason you couldn't

170
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:38,240
pay the lesson fees.

171
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,100
I knew

172
00:06:39,370 --> 00:06:40,970
you'd never take that money.

173
00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:42,360
I thought...

174
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:44,010
after getting the pay,

175
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:46,020
I'd give it straight to Mr. Zheng.

176
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:48,740
I knew this thing

177
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:50,200
must still be on your mind.

178
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,690
Didn't I tell you?

179
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:53,820
It's normal to lose money in business.

180
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:54,870
Besides,

181
00:06:54,870 --> 00:06:55,430
that was not

182
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:56,350
up to you to decide.

183
00:06:56,350 --> 00:06:58,350
I just can't stop thinking about it.

184
00:06:59,740 --> 00:07:00,690
It weighs heavily

185
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:01,560
on my heart.

186
00:07:04,570 --> 00:07:05,970
Then after today's talk,

187
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:07,180
let's not bring it up again,

188
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:07,630
okay?

189
00:07:13,930 --> 00:07:15,480
I know it's absolutely impossible for you

190
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,740
to forget it entirely.

191
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,780
How about this?

192
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:22,070
When we all sort out

193
00:07:22,070 --> 00:07:22,940
our matters,

194
00:07:23,370 --> 00:07:24,620
I won't stop you from giving me

195
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:25,480
even 80% of your pay

196
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,740
from writing scripts.

197
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,930
Anyway, you must not strain yourself

198
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:29,390
to do

199
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:31,050
such dangerous things again.

200
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:32,950
That'll work.

201
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:34,670
It's a good idea.

202
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,159
Dig in.

203
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:43,600
You too.

204
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:51,580
Listen,

205
00:07:51,890 --> 00:07:53,090
don't worry about me.

206
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:54,430
Today, I'm here to tell you

207
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:55,290
some good news.

208
00:07:57,950 --> 00:07:58,890
I got a job.

209
00:07:58,920 --> 00:07:59,530
Really?

210
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,450
What kind of job?

211
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,630
Mrs. Zheng referred me

212
00:08:02,630 --> 00:08:04,070
for a position as a designer's assistant

213
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:05,270
in a costume company.

214
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:06,540
I don't know much about it,

215
00:08:06,540 --> 00:08:08,940
but I'll treat it
as a learning experience.

216
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:10,450
T-T-That is amazing.

217
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:12,530
H-How much does it pay?

218
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,580
Nine hundred a month after probation.

219
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,270
Nine hundred?

220
00:08:19,610 --> 00:08:20,610
What do you think?

221
00:08:21,630 --> 00:08:23,180
Incredible. Truly incredible.

222
00:08:23,180 --> 00:08:24,840
T-Then you must try your best.

223
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:25,330
Well,

224
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:27,220
I have experience
since I used to be an assisant.

225
00:08:27,220 --> 00:08:28,750
No, I mean I learned my lesson from it.

226
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,240
But I can still share it with you.

227
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,120
I already know every bit

228
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,520
of what you went through.

229
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,169
That's true.

230
00:08:34,860 --> 00:08:35,600
You're amazing,

231
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,330
and you can do everything well.

232
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,980
Let this be an early celebration.

233
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:41,830
I wish you every success

234
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:44,320
in your first job, Designer Zhuang!

235
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:45,850
To success!

236
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:54,410
Why must you bring up the past?

237
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:55,390
W-Who are you?

238
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,330
What are you doing here?

239
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:03,680
I'm talking to you!

240
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:07,600
Did you miss me?

241
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:10,480
I'm back,

242
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:13,400
buddies!

243
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:15,440
Cao?

244
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:16,420
Heretic Cao?

245
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:18,220
-You... You little punk!
-Zongbao.

246
00:09:18,220 --> 00:09:18,740
Liangliang!

247
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:20,320
-Why are you back?
-Liangliang, Liangliang!

248
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:20,910
Coming!

249
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:21,290
Shengli.

250
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:21,700
What?

251
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:23,450
What were you doing?

252
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,480
Look who's back!

253
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,500
Where have you been?

254
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:26,240
I just spent

255
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:27,290
the previous few days outside

256
00:09:27,290 --> 00:09:28,890
reflecting on my life and...

257
00:09:29,130 --> 00:09:29,860
Liangliang.

258
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:31,950
I missed you.

259
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:39,880
I really missed you guys.

260
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:41,360
Liangliang,

261
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:42,290
I missed you lot.

262
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:43,100
I missed you lot.

263
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:43,560
Wait.

264
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:45,950
W-Where did your hair go?

265
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,340
It was cut off and gone

266
00:09:48,410 --> 00:09:49,120
with my dignity

267
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,180
and perseverance.

268
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,220
Do I look good?

269
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:52,240
You had dignity?

270
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,200
Grab weapons!

271
00:09:53,910 --> 00:09:54,410
No!

272
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,170
Your job's also so exhausting?

273
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:11,390
Your schedule is almost as crazy as mine.

274
00:10:11,390 --> 00:10:12,050
Say no more.

275
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:13,890
Now I finally realize

276
00:10:13,890 --> 00:10:15,350
how hard it's been for you.

277
00:10:17,860 --> 00:10:18,390
Oh right.

278
00:10:19,370 --> 00:10:20,410
You are well-read.

279
00:10:20,410 --> 00:10:21,810
Can you make a list for me?

280
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:22,630
Sure.

281
00:10:22,790 --> 00:10:23,790
What kind of list?

282
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:25,120
Just a list of books

283
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,460
on design, art, and literature.

284
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:27,060
Anything.

285
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,050
You need to read these books
to do your job

286
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:30,240
as a designer's assistant?

287
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,170
Tell me about it.

288
00:10:32,010 --> 00:10:33,370
Up till now, I even haven't met

289
00:10:33,370 --> 00:10:34,300
with Ms. Yue yet.

290
00:10:35,290 --> 00:10:37,600
She's quite strange, indeed.

291
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,180
If Ms. Yue

292
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:41,010
somehow gets together

293
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:41,960
with Mr. He,

294
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,460
won't it be fun?

295
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:45,460
You just love the drama, don't you?

296
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:47,010
No, I'm just being curious.

297
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:48,530
Don't worry.

298
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:49,450
I promise

299
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:51,570
to draw on all my knowledge and abilities

300
00:10:51,570 --> 00:10:52,470
to make a clear

301
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,750
and thorough list for you.

302
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:56,350
Thank you then,
Mr. Xu the great screenwriter.

303
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:57,680
You're welcome.

304
00:10:58,420 --> 00:10:59,300
As it happens,

305
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,960
I need a favor from you too.

306
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:01,960
What is it?

307
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:04,410
A character

308
00:11:04,410 --> 00:11:06,120
in the script that Mr. He is writing

309
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,600
is a tailor.

310
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:09,580
He doesn't think my portrayal of it
is accurate enough.

311
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:11,550
I only know a little bit
about this profession.

312
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:12,630
My portrayal of it is indeed

313
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,890
distant with reality.

314
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:15,350
That's easy.

315
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,740
You can consult my mom.

316
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:18,950
N-no need.

317
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:20,530
R-Really, no. I-I-I...

318
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:21,930
I can just interview you.

319
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,270
Or you can

320
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:25,890
interview your mother in my stead.

321
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:26,890
That's no good.

322
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:28,790
You need a real tailor's opnion.

323
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:29,650
My mom is a professional.

324
00:11:29,650 --> 00:11:30,290
I'm not.

325
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:35,200
T-Then fine.

326
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:36,720
I'll write your mother

327
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:37,460
a letter later.

328
00:11:37,460 --> 00:11:38,720
Why write her a letter?

329
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,400
Isn't there a phone here?

330
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,400
You can call her anytime.

331
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:50,910
Why don't you do it now?

332
00:11:50,910 --> 00:11:51,900
N-No, not now.

333
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,550
I need to make a draft first.

334
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:54,290
No, not a draft.

335
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:55,890
I must make an interview outline

336
00:11:55,890 --> 00:11:56,630
first.

337
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:01,700
M- Making an interview outline

338
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:02,940
is perfectly normal.

339
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,970
Why did you drink so much again?

340
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,100
Take this.

341
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,000
Zhuang.

342
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:34,050
Do you think

343
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:36,200
I'm a good actress?

344
00:12:36,650 --> 00:12:37,650
Of course you are.

345
00:12:37,950 --> 00:12:39,210
Do you even need to ask?

346
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:43,270
Mr. Chu said the same thing.

347
00:12:44,860 --> 00:12:46,280
You drank with him again?

348
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:48,320
It was practically an honor.

349
00:12:49,940 --> 00:12:50,940
How could I not go?

350
00:12:54,370 --> 00:12:54,770
You've

351
00:12:54,770 --> 00:12:56,360
drunk with him so many times.

352
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:57,890
Have you secured any roles?

353
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,040
He didn't confirm anything.

354
00:13:02,980 --> 00:13:04,710
If you keep drinking like this,

355
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,240
your health will be ruined.

356
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,970
I don't want to drink like this.

357
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,060
But time is all I have.

358
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:15,910
Trading time for an opportunity...

359
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:17,890
is worthwhile.

360
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:37,830
What now?

361
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:41,630
I...

362
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,010
My throat feels a bit tight.

363
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:53,550
[Registration Room]

364
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:47,760
It's not like you're going to
sing to my mom.

365
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:49,860
Then let's quit.

366
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:50,990
No, please call her.

367
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:52,310
Do it.

368
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:54,700
You sure?

369
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:55,120
Yes.

370
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:12,870
How about we...

371
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:14,860
Hey, Mom.

372
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,650
I'm calling for what I told you yesterday.

373
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,050
Shengli will talk to you.

374
00:14:21,050 --> 00:14:22,380
Chat with her a bit more.

375
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,930
Phone calls are expensive.

376
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:24,900
Hurry.

377
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:31,160
Hello, auntie.

378
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:32,400
Yes, right.

379
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:34,190
This is Xu Shengli.

380
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:35,520
Exactly, yes.

381
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:37,890
How have you been, auntie?

382
00:14:39,790 --> 00:14:40,880
That's good.

383
00:14:41,890 --> 00:14:42,750
Zhuang Zhuang?

384
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,650
Learning to sing
does take a lot out of her,

385
00:14:46,510 --> 00:14:48,040
but she sings beautifully.

386
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:50,140
Everyone here loves to hear her sing.

387
00:14:50,620 --> 00:14:52,080
She sings for us every day.

388
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:53,460
When she sings too much,

389
00:14:53,460 --> 00:14:54,520
s-she gets hungry.

390
00:14:54,650 --> 00:14:56,310
Her meals are going fine, too.

391
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,350
She eats a lot.

392
00:14:57,380 --> 00:14:58,310
Get to the point.

393
00:14:58,940 --> 00:14:59,980
Just don't worry.

394
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:02,690
Yes.

395
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,290
I was just talking to her about it.

396
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:04,840
I said,

397
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:05,720
I must

398
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:07,600
visit Wenzhou if there is a chance,

399
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:10,260
for the wonderful landscapes there.

400
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,260
There is a...

401
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:12,410
What mountain is it?

402
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:13,550
Right!

403
00:15:13,570 --> 00:15:14,770
That exact mountain!

404
00:15:15,810 --> 00:15:16,410
Yes.

405
00:15:16,450 --> 00:15:18,070
What a place of stunning scenery,
fresh air,

406
00:15:18,070 --> 00:15:19,200
and perfect humidity.

407
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,800
It's too dry here in Beijing.

408
00:15:23,410 --> 00:15:24,270
My parents?

409
00:15:24,740 --> 00:15:25,940
They are doing quite well.

410
00:15:24,910 --> 00:15:25,600
[List of Questions]

411
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:26,450
[People all like Dacron
and knickerbockers]

412
00:15:25,990 --> 00:15:26,770
They are both in Shandong.

413
00:15:26,470 --> 00:15:27,490
[Which kind of fabric
do people order most from your shop?]

414
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:29,090
[What do customers especially care about
when they choose fabrics?]

415
00:15:28,220 --> 00:15:29,540
They're also in good health.

416
00:15:29,540 --> 00:15:31,140
Just don't worry, auntie.

417
00:15:33,010 --> 00:15:34,620
Well, I take good care of her.

418
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:35,440
Everyone here

419
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:36,700
takes good care of her.

420
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:37,580
Right.

421
00:15:37,580 --> 00:15:38,890
That's mainly because she is nice

422
00:15:38,890 --> 00:15:40,090
to everyone here too.

423
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:41,580
Yes, just be assured.

424
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,010
Enough. Cut to the chase.

425
00:15:46,010 --> 00:15:47,390
I-I do have a question.

426
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:47,950
Well,

427
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:49,170
auntie, may I ask something?

428
00:15:49,170 --> 00:15:50,590
Suppose you meet

429
00:15:50,770 --> 00:15:52,130
an extremely difficult client

430
00:15:52,130 --> 00:15:53,300
during

431
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:54,200
the sales process,

432
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,440
then

433
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:56,650
h-how would you

434
00:15:56,670 --> 00:15:57,620
usually

435
00:15:57,670 --> 00:15:58,870
decline them?

436
00:16:00,050 --> 00:16:01,540
Auntie, wait a second.

437
00:16:01,650 --> 00:16:02,580
I'll take notes.

438
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,680
Go ahead, please.

439
00:16:08,010 --> 00:16:12,530
[Registration Room]

440
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:37,670
You've been laughing since yesterday.

441
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:39,620
You asked my mom

442
00:16:39,620 --> 00:16:41,080
what she had for dinner the night before.

443
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:42,290
What were you thinking?

444
00:16:42,290 --> 00:16:43,080
I was just showing care

445
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,790
for her on your behalf, wasn't I?

446
00:16:44,790 --> 00:16:45,730
You have no idea.

447
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,480
Nowadays, many older family members

448
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:48,620
at home would skip dinner

449
00:16:48,620 --> 00:16:49,680
just to save money.

450
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:50,810
That's no good.

451
00:16:53,150 --> 00:16:54,810
So you did plan to ask her that.

452
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:56,870
O-Of course.

453
00:16:58,670 --> 00:16:59,550
Then, did that call

454
00:16:59,550 --> 00:17:01,720
solve the problem you met
in writing the script?

455
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:02,860
It gave me huge help.

456
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:03,270
Listen,

457
00:17:03,270 --> 00:17:04,109
next time I see your mother,

458
00:17:04,109 --> 00:17:05,510
I must thank her properly.

459
00:17:05,510 --> 00:17:06,980
You should first thank her daughter

460
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:07,660
properly.

461
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,880
That's a must.

462
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,740
Today, I'll go ask Mr. He

463
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:11,569
for a permission

464
00:17:11,569 --> 00:17:13,910
to add a special thanks in the script

465
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,660
to the beautiful and kind
Ms. Zhuang Zhuang.

466
00:17:18,849 --> 00:17:19,900
Why don't you just change

467
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,069
the character's name

468
00:17:21,069 --> 00:17:21,810
to mine?

469
00:17:22,109 --> 00:17:22,550
No way.

470
00:17:23,030 --> 00:17:24,069
N-Not a chance.

471
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,010
Why?

472
00:17:25,569 --> 00:17:27,500
She and her love in the script
end up splitting up.

473
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,160
It's a jinx.

474
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:38,060
You...

475
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:40,200
L-Let me go get you

476
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:40,850
that list.

477
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,450
Not this one.

478
00:17:57,050 --> 00:17:57,660
Here it is.

479
00:17:58,720 --> 00:17:59,470
Take a look.

480
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:01,500
I have the ones

481
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,500
with checkmarks.

482
00:18:02,770 --> 00:18:05,050
You'll have to find the rest
in the library.

483
00:18:05,050 --> 00:18:06,350
Let me know when you go there.

484
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:08,950
These many books are too heavy
for you to carry.

485
00:18:11,670 --> 00:18:13,200
Can't I borrow one at a time?

486
00:18:14,850 --> 00:18:15,850
That's an option.

487
00:18:16,310 --> 00:18:17,510
How brilliant of you.

488
00:18:18,950 --> 00:18:20,640
Thanks, Mr. Xu the great screenwriter.

489
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,400
No problem.

490
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:33,400
Why is there no one here today?

491
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,080
Where are they?

492
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:34,810
Liangliang.

493
00:18:35,810 --> 00:18:37,220
The kitchen drain is clogged.

494
00:18:37,220 --> 00:18:39,010
Mr. Tao is having a plumper fix it.

495
00:18:39,010 --> 00:18:39,540
All done.

496
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:40,900
It's unclogged now.

497
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:41,390
Good.

498
00:18:41,420 --> 00:18:42,950
Let me sweep this up for you.

499
00:18:43,210 --> 00:18:44,480
Thank you.

500
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,350
Thanks.

501
00:18:46,010 --> 00:18:46,540
Alright.

502
00:18:48,570 --> 00:18:48,900
Done.

503
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:50,660
Thanks for your hard work.

504
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:51,190
Anytime.

505
00:18:51,350 --> 00:18:51,680
Okay.

506
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:53,170
Let me walk you out.

507
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:54,170
Alright.

508
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:55,140
Okay.

509
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:55,550
I-I'll put it here.

510
00:18:55,550 --> 00:18:56,090
Thanks for the hard work.

511
00:18:56,090 --> 00:18:57,690
Alright, let me walk you out.

512
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:58,500
Thanks again.

513
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:00,480
No need to see me off.

514
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:01,510
-Okay.
-Zongbao!

515
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,290
What brings you to our place?

516
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:06,290
This is our place.

517
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:07,700
I-I didn't know.

518
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:08,780
You didn't know?

519
00:19:09,350 --> 00:19:11,080
I hired him to fix the plumbing.

520
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:13,480
Dad,

521
00:19:13,530 --> 00:19:14,110
he's the man

522
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:15,370
I often told you about,

523
00:19:15,770 --> 00:19:16,790
who treated me

524
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,180
very nicely in the hostel,

525
00:19:18,180 --> 00:19:19,240
named Guo Zongbao.

526
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:20,680
It is him exactly.

527
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:22,070
He's not a plumber.

528
00:19:22,460 --> 00:19:23,060
Uncle Tao.

529
00:19:24,700 --> 00:19:25,500
He's an actor.

530
00:19:26,660 --> 00:19:28,980
Doing research by living the life,
aren't you?

531
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:30,190
W-What a coincidence.

532
00:19:30,190 --> 00:19:31,320
So random to run into

533
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:33,500
[Welcome]

534
00:19:31,350 --> 00:19:32,720
a friend of yours, Liangliang.

535
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,460
I just stewed a pot of pork shoulder.

536
00:19:34,460 --> 00:19:36,010
How about I cook a few more dishes?

537
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:37,200
Everyone stay for a meal.

538
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,070
Uncle Tao...

539
00:19:38,070 --> 00:19:38,730
Just stay.

540
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:40,330
My dad is a great cook.

541
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,570
He makes amazing

542
00:19:41,570 --> 00:19:42,160
pork shoulder.

543
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:42,550
Come on.

544
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:43,700
I-I have to leave.

545
00:19:45,570 --> 00:19:46,830
Let my dad cook for you.

546
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,270
-Liangliang...
-Say no more.

547
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:49,670
Nothing needs to be said.

548
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:50,720
I understand.

549
00:19:51,830 --> 00:19:52,890
A drink at my place?

550
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:55,720
I-I should...

551
00:19:57,550 --> 00:19:59,530
-Come on, Zongbao!
-Fine, okay.

552
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:05,530
Repairing range hoods!

553
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:09,350
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

554
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:08,220
Repairing range hoods!

555
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,730
Unclogging drains!

556
00:20:10,890 --> 00:20:15,660
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

557
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:14,590
Repairing range hoods!

558
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:15,320
Liangliang.

559
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:16,810
Well,

560
00:20:17,330 --> 00:20:19,250
I need to park the bike

561
00:20:19,310 --> 00:20:20,250
over there.

562
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:22,330
I'm not going any further this way.

563
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:23,200
I'll park the bike first

564
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:28,550
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

565
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:24,890
and then go home.

566
00:20:25,010 --> 00:20:26,090
You should've said it earlier,

567
00:20:26,090 --> 00:20:27,480
so you didn't have to
walk such a long way with me.

568
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:28,080
It's okay.

569
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:29,520
Easy does it.

570
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,920
Don't go to work again.

571
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:33,230
Listen, Liangliang,

572
00:20:34,090 --> 00:20:35,400
please don't tell anyone

573
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,660
what happened today.

574
00:20:37,350 --> 00:20:38,020
I know.

575
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:40,360
Nobody will know it

576
00:20:40,610 --> 00:20:41,680
if we both keep it secret.

577
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:44,480
You're just experiencing real life
for your acting.

578
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:46,010
Zongbao, I have a question.

579
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,140
Back in the hostel,

580
00:20:48,770 --> 00:20:50,970
you told us stories from your hometown.

581
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:52,960
Are they all true?

582
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:53,960
Yes, all true.

583
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,460
You do have a wife

584
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:56,610
and a child, right?

585
00:20:58,010 --> 00:20:59,410
Yes, I have photos.

586
00:20:59,510 --> 00:21:00,170
Okay, okay.

587
00:21:00,510 --> 00:21:01,850
As long as they're all true.

588
00:21:01,850 --> 00:21:03,250
Don't make them up as part

589
00:21:03,330 --> 00:21:04,510
of your preparation for acting.

590
00:21:04,510 --> 00:21:05,700
Raising a family is a serious matter.

591
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:07,030
You must want a beating.

592
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,380
I have to go.

593
00:21:08,810 --> 00:21:09,610
Go home early.

594
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:10,550
Sure, sure.

595
00:21:12,850 --> 00:21:13,520
Off I go.

596
00:21:14,220 --> 00:21:15,350
I'll head home soon.

597
00:21:15,740 --> 00:21:16,980
Just return the bike.

598
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:18,550
Don't go to work again.

599
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:19,870
Got it. I won't.

600
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:21,960
Go home.

601
00:21:29,270 --> 00:21:32,290
-Repairing range hoods!
-Look at that.

602
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:35,000
Unclogging drains!

603
00:21:36,530 --> 00:21:37,390
Zhuang Zhuang.

604
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,590
How are things at Ms. Yue's office

605
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:39,290
lately?

606
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:40,170
Pretty good.

607
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,060
My friend

608
00:21:42,090 --> 00:21:42,830
told me Ms. Yue has

609
00:21:42,830 --> 00:21:43,960
an odd disposition.

610
00:21:44,010 --> 00:21:44,850
Whatever she says to you,

611
00:21:44,850 --> 00:21:46,110
don't take it to heart.

612
00:21:46,460 --> 00:21:47,790
I'm practically an amateur.

613
00:21:47,790 --> 00:21:48,590
So, I'm taking

614
00:21:49,030 --> 00:21:50,600
this time to study hard

615
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:51,920
and get fully prepared.

616
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:52,770
I'm back!

617
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:54,920
-Mr. Zheng.
-Mrs. Zheng,

618
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:55,980
is Zhuang Zhuang here?

619
00:21:55,980 --> 00:21:56,640
Yes, she is.

620
00:21:57,270 --> 00:21:59,270
-She arrived early.
-Already here?

621
00:21:59,270 --> 00:22:00,500
Let me tell you something.

622
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:00,960
Come on.

623
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:01,570
Sit down first.

624
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:02,180
Okay.

625
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:04,110
What is it? You seem happy.

626
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:06,330
Tomorrow night,

627
00:22:06,380 --> 00:22:07,510
there will be a show,

628
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:09,320
including

629
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,690
a female quartet.

630
00:22:10,850 --> 00:22:11,880
But now, all of a sudden,

631
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:12,880
one of the singers

632
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:13,990
has fallen sick

633
00:22:14,090 --> 00:22:15,150
and cannot make it.

634
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:17,500
I was asked to find someone
to replace her.

635
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:18,300
I'm wondering

636
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,040
if you'd like to give it a try.

637
00:22:20,460 --> 00:22:21,450
Yes, I'd love to!

638
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,290
-No, no.
-Of course I'd love to!

639
00:22:22,290 --> 00:22:22,890
No, no way.

640
00:22:22,980 --> 00:22:23,780
I object to it.

641
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:25,110
For what reason?

642
00:22:25,220 --> 00:22:25,880
How can Zhuang Zhuang

643
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:27,310
be someone's replacement?

644
00:22:27,310 --> 00:22:27,810
That won't do.

645
00:22:27,810 --> 00:22:28,240
It's not like that.

646
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:28,880
It is. You...

647
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:30,070
Please hear me out.

648
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,100
The troupe is recruiting right now.

649
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:34,430
If Zhuang Zhuang performs well this time,

650
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:35,400
there will be tons

651
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,600
of opportunities for her in the future.

652
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:40,160
Mrs. Zheng, I want to go.
I'd love to do it.

653
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:41,110
Fine.

654
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:42,940
Whatever Zhuang Zhuang wants to do.

655
00:22:42,940 --> 00:22:43,970
Break a leg!

656
00:22:45,170 --> 00:22:46,370
Thank you, Mr. Zheng.

657
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,790
It's nothing.

658
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:51,400
Master, how have your eyes been lately?

659
00:22:52,590 --> 00:22:53,850
Sometimes good, and sometimes bad.

660
00:22:53,850 --> 00:22:55,150
Don't worry about me.

661
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:57,720
For your good-looking friend's

662
00:22:57,770 --> 00:22:58,900
first performance,

663
00:22:59,460 --> 00:23:01,060
you must dress up nicely.

664
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:14,960
Now, you look...

665
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,430
a bit like me back in the day.

666
00:23:19,510 --> 00:23:20,530
Years ago,

667
00:23:20,550 --> 00:23:22,310
a director told me

668
00:23:23,460 --> 00:23:24,720
that in the whole crew,

669
00:23:24,850 --> 00:23:26,110
including the actors,

670
00:23:26,330 --> 00:23:28,990
the most handsome one was me,
the screenwriter.

671
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:31,200
The director must have had a problem

672
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,130
with the actors.

673
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:33,440
If you were the best-looking one,

674
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:34,590
the actors must look terrible, right?

675
00:23:34,590 --> 00:23:35,660
What's that gibberish?

676
00:23:35,660 --> 00:23:37,270
The suit. Mind the suit!

677
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,470
Right, right.

678
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:46,100
I wore this about ten years ago

679
00:23:46,720 --> 00:23:48,130
when I attended

680
00:23:48,220 --> 00:23:50,550
the premiere of my work
for the first time.

681
00:23:51,940 --> 00:23:53,270
It's been over a decade.

682
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,550
I don't have a son,

683
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:58,900
so lucky you.

684
00:24:04,790 --> 00:24:05,250
Thanks.

685
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:27,100
[Please line up to board
and let passengers off first]

686
00:24:36,670 --> 00:24:45,170
[The Voice of Classics]

687
00:24:37,330 --> 00:24:41,480
Wild geese are flying south.

688
00:24:41,770 --> 00:24:45,940
Wild geese are flying south.

689
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:54,220
The cries of wild geese break my heart.

690
00:24:54,850 --> 00:24:59,940
Though you're only leaving today,

691
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:06,710
I am already yearning for your return
in spring.

692
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:14,570
I am already yearning for your return
in spring.

693
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:19,610
After you depart today,

694
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:25,270
do come back in spring.

695
00:25:26,110 --> 00:25:28,700
I long for your return.

696
00:25:30,250 --> 00:25:35,920
Don't shatter my heart.

697
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:45,310
Don't shatter my heart.

698
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:55,550
I await your return in spring.

699
00:25:46,170 --> 00:25:51,530
[The Voice of Classics]

700
00:25:56,380 --> 00:26:00,750
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

701
00:26:02,620 --> 00:26:06,040
[The Voice of Classics]

702
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:10,200
[The Voice of Classics by the Art Troupe]

703
00:26:07,660 --> 00:26:09,750
This theater is no good.

704
00:26:10,220 --> 00:26:14,810
[In full bloom in Beiyin Concert Hall]

705
00:26:10,310 --> 00:26:11,220
They won't let friends

706
00:26:11,220 --> 00:26:12,820
and relatives go backstage.

707
00:26:12,830 --> 00:26:14,770
H-How do we present these flowers
to Zhuang?

708
00:26:14,770 --> 00:26:16,000
Look how antsy Shengli is.

709
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,010
I'm not antsy at all.

710
00:26:17,010 --> 00:26:18,340
We'll see her soon.

711
00:26:18,530 --> 00:26:19,770
Zhuang Zhuang is a substitute.

712
00:26:19,770 --> 00:26:20,640
It makes sense

713
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:21,250
that they won't let us in.

714
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:22,580
She'll be out here soon.

715
00:26:25,460 --> 00:26:26,250
Zhuang Zhuang is out now.

716
00:26:26,250 --> 00:26:27,110
Zhuang Zhuang!

717
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:28,240
Zhuang Zhuang!

718
00:26:28,460 --> 00:26:28,900
Zhuang!

719
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:29,270
Zhuang Zhuang.

720
00:26:29,270 --> 00:26:30,310
-Wait a sec!
-Here!

721
00:26:30,310 --> 00:26:31,320
Great work today.

722
00:26:31,380 --> 00:26:32,270
Cheer her on, shall we?

723
00:26:32,270 --> 00:26:33,190
Sure, let's cheer her on.

724
00:26:33,190 --> 00:26:35,000
-Zhuang Zhuang!
-Zhuang Zhuang!

725
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,060
Congratulations.

726
00:26:36,140 --> 00:26:36,960
Thanks.

727
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:37,820
Zhuang Zhuang!

728
00:26:38,570 --> 00:26:40,610
-Zhuang Zhuang!
-Zhuang Zhuang!

729
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:41,920
How about we take a photo?

730
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:46,520
[Beiyin Concert Hall]

731
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:43,270
Yes, let's take a photo.

732
00:26:43,270 --> 00:26:43,900
That guy...

733
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:44,680
has a camera, so he must know

734
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:45,180
how to take photos.

735
00:26:45,180 --> 00:26:46,510
-That one.
-Hey, buddy!

736
00:26:46,570 --> 00:26:48,160
I could hear you sing even outside.

737
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,690
Could you take a photo of us?

738
00:26:49,740 --> 00:26:50,240
Sure.

739
00:26:50,420 --> 00:26:51,470
Thank you so much.

740
00:26:51,510 --> 00:26:52,380
Thanks for the help.

741
00:26:52,380 --> 00:26:53,530
Get the banner above in the frame too.

742
00:26:53,530 --> 00:26:54,240
This banner?

743
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:58,090
[Beiyin Concert Hall]

744
00:26:54,250 --> 00:26:54,780
Exactly.

745
00:26:55,350 --> 00:26:55,950
Thank you.

746
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:56,920
This spot is good.

747
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:57,810
Mr. Xu, hurry.

748
00:26:57,810 --> 00:26:59,590
-D-Don't forget the banner.
-Come over now.

749
00:26:59,590 --> 00:27:00,200
He's waiting.

750
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,290
Come here quickly, Liangliang!

751
00:27:01,290 --> 00:27:02,200
Come on.

752
00:27:02,290 --> 00:27:02,890
Get ready.

753
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:06,930
Look here, everyone.

754
00:27:06,980 --> 00:27:08,380
Keep your smiles on.

755
00:27:08,590 --> 00:27:11,590
Alright. Three, two, one!

756
00:27:11,830 --> 00:27:12,240
Done.

757
00:27:12,290 --> 00:27:12,640
Great.

758
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:13,140
Thank you.

759
00:27:13,140 --> 00:27:13,930
Many thanks.

760
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:14,900
What now?

761
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:15,760
Get back there.

762
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:17,290
You and John should take a photo.

763
00:27:17,290 --> 00:27:18,570
-Just go.
-Let's get a photo of you two.

764
00:27:18,570 --> 00:27:19,850
Hurry.

765
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:21,960
Don't be shy. Get closer.

766
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:23,220
Saving that space for someone
to stand between you, huh?

767
00:27:23,220 --> 00:27:23,880
Put on a smile!

768
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:25,850
I-Is someone going to stand between you?

769
00:27:25,850 --> 00:27:26,650
Right. Closer

770
00:27:26,770 --> 00:27:27,570
to each other.

771
00:27:28,510 --> 00:27:29,220
Smile!

772
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:31,530
What are you doing?

773
00:27:31,530 --> 00:27:32,460
Guys, catch him!

774
00:27:32,530 --> 00:27:34,460
What kind of motorcyclist are you?

775
00:27:38,220 --> 00:27:39,420
-Is that guy blind or what?
-Where did you get hurt?

776
00:27:39,420 --> 00:27:39,920
Shengli!

777
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:40,500
Where did you get hit?

778
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:41,090
The leg or the foot?

779
00:27:41,090 --> 00:27:42,660
Don't move me or touch it.

780
00:27:43,570 --> 00:27:44,190
Shengli,

781
00:27:44,380 --> 00:27:45,110
are you okay?

782
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:46,240
That motorcyclist

783
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:47,700
seemed to be Kang Shunyin.

784
00:27:47,700 --> 00:27:48,500
Kang Shunyin?

785
00:27:49,330 --> 00:27:51,220
-Let's take him to the hospital now.
-Hurry.

786
00:27:51,220 --> 00:27:53,080
-To the hospital.
-Hurry, get up.

787
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:54,070
Don't put weight on your foot.

788
00:27:54,070 --> 00:27:54,710
Hop up.

789
00:27:54,900 --> 00:27:55,330
Careful.

790
00:27:55,330 --> 00:27:56,290
A bit higher up the back.

791
00:27:56,290 --> 00:27:56,820
Let's go.

792
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:00,350
Nice and slow.

793
00:28:00,350 --> 00:28:01,600
It hurts!

794
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:02,290
Hurry.

795
00:28:02,290 --> 00:28:03,660
Put his feet on the bed.

796
00:28:03,750 --> 00:28:06,350
-Such suffering for Xu.
-This is the good foot.

797
00:28:06,530 --> 00:28:08,530
Slowly. Don't let it get hurt again.

798
00:28:09,050 --> 00:28:10,250
-Come on.
-Lean back.

799
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:12,250
Let's save a beautiful memory.

800
00:28:12,250 --> 00:28:13,180
One, two, three!

801
00:28:13,380 --> 00:28:14,550
Zongbao, get closer to him.

802
00:28:14,550 --> 00:28:15,870
Don't waste the film.

803
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,880
-Get that foot in the frame.
-One more photo, with the foot in.

804
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:18,810
One, two, three!

805
00:28:20,460 --> 00:28:20,860
Done.

806
00:28:21,090 --> 00:28:21,590
All done.

807
00:28:21,590 --> 00:28:22,120
Alright.

808
00:28:22,790 --> 00:28:23,770
Today, if it hadn't been for

809
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:24,810
my leather shoes and jeans

810
00:28:24,810 --> 00:28:25,810
restraining me from taking

811
00:28:25,810 --> 00:28:27,400
big steps, I would've caught that guy!

812
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,380
If that's what you're saying,

813
00:28:28,380 --> 00:28:29,610
I'd say it happened so suddenly

814
00:28:29,610 --> 00:28:30,180
that it caught me off guard.

815
00:28:30,180 --> 00:28:31,310
Otherwise, I could've pulled him down

816
00:28:31,310 --> 00:28:32,080
before you went after him, right?

817
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:34,160
I'm telling you, that guy is brutal,

818
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:34,660
isn't he?

819
00:28:34,660 --> 00:28:35,900
Look what he did to Shengli.

820
00:28:35,900 --> 00:28:37,090
-Xu Shengli.
-Officer Tang.

821
00:28:37,090 --> 00:28:37,890
Officer Tang.

822
00:28:38,290 --> 00:28:38,790
Officer Tang.

823
00:28:38,790 --> 00:28:39,990
Is your foot alright?

824
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:41,480
Yes,

825
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:42,350
it's fine.

826
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,100
I just found out

827
00:28:44,270 --> 00:28:44,900
that Kang Shunyin

828
00:28:44,900 --> 00:28:46,350
had attacked more than once.

829
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:48,080
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

830
00:28:49,180 --> 00:28:50,310
That was because...

831
00:28:52,050 --> 00:28:53,710
we didn't want to trouble you.

832
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:56,080
A sensible citizen, aren't you?

833
00:28:56,530 --> 00:28:58,030
Later, I'll go to the pricinct

834
00:28:58,030 --> 00:28:59,290
to report this matter.

835
00:28:59,750 --> 00:29:01,950
His behavior this time was outrageous.

836
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:03,940
We will definitely take action.

837
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:06,040
From now on,

838
00:29:06,180 --> 00:29:06,790
he won't disturb

839
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:07,750
your life anymore.

840
00:29:07,750 --> 00:29:08,550
Rest assured.

841
00:29:08,980 --> 00:29:10,380
Thank you, Officer Tang.

842
00:29:11,270 --> 00:29:12,310
It's not easy for a girl to make

843
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:13,440
a living in Beijing.

844
00:29:13,530 --> 00:29:14,640
But don't fret if anything happens.

845
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:15,880
Just turn to the police.

846
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:16,420
Got it?

847
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:17,640
Got it.

848
00:29:18,420 --> 00:29:18,950
Alright.

849
00:29:19,380 --> 00:29:20,400
Take good care of him.

850
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:20,960
I'm leaving then.

851
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:21,420
Thank you.

852
00:29:21,420 --> 00:29:22,110
Goodbye, Officer Tang.

853
00:29:22,110 --> 00:29:22,760
Take care.

854
00:29:22,940 --> 00:29:24,200
Sorry for the trouble.

855
00:29:24,290 --> 00:29:25,420
It's also not easy for a young man

856
00:29:25,420 --> 00:29:26,950
to make a living in Beijing.

857
00:29:30,380 --> 00:29:31,240
Does it hurt?

858
00:29:32,810 --> 00:29:33,410
Not at all.

859
00:29:33,790 --> 00:29:35,050
It doesn't hurt at all.

860
00:29:36,770 --> 00:29:38,010
He was howling in pain just now,

861
00:29:38,010 --> 00:29:39,810
and he's all fine at this moment.

862
00:29:41,850 --> 00:29:43,460
Don't take their nonsense seriously.

863
00:29:43,460 --> 00:29:44,720
I'm really not in pain.

864
00:29:52,310 --> 00:29:53,310
It's all my fault.

865
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:54,550
How are you going

866
00:29:54,550 --> 00:29:56,220
to write scripts
when you're injured like this?

867
00:29:56,220 --> 00:29:58,200
I-I don't write with my feet.

868
00:29:58,240 --> 00:29:59,000
I'm really fine.

869
00:29:59,000 --> 00:29:59,930
Look at my hands.

870
00:29:59,940 --> 00:30:01,600
Perfectly fine, aren't they?

871
00:30:03,850 --> 00:30:05,180
It really doesn't hurt.

872
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,530
It doesn't. Look.

873
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:10,610
I'm really fine.

874
00:30:38,310 --> 00:30:39,440
Take your medicine.

875
00:30:58,830 --> 00:31:00,830
Can't you let me pose properly
for a photo?

876
00:31:00,830 --> 00:31:02,490
You look great no matter what.

877
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:05,140
Your eyes are red.

878
00:31:05,220 --> 00:31:06,380
Your nose is red.

879
00:31:07,010 --> 00:31:08,270
Y-You're just pretty.

880
00:31:10,350 --> 00:31:11,130
Lie down now.

881
00:31:11,380 --> 00:31:13,380
Or your foot won't get enough blood.

882
00:31:18,980 --> 00:31:19,440
Come on.

883
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:27,400
Are you feeling better?

884
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:28,010
Yes.

885
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:29,510
Sure.

886
00:31:32,010 --> 00:31:33,690
You were especially stunning

887
00:31:34,980 --> 00:31:35,840
on stage today.

888
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:45,610
I got the smallest part in today's show,

889
00:31:45,610 --> 00:31:47,740
but you guys were still so supportive.

890
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:49,160
That deeply moved me.

891
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:50,770
In our eyes,

892
00:31:50,790 --> 00:31:52,120
you were singing a solo.

893
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:53,550
We could see no one on stage,

894
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:54,200
but you.

895
00:31:54,250 --> 00:31:56,250
We couldn't even hear anyone else sing.

896
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:56,610
Okay.

897
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:59,480
So your mouth isn't injured.

898
00:32:02,830 --> 00:32:03,610
I'm sure you will

899
00:32:03,610 --> 00:32:06,670
have tons of opportunities
to sing solos in the future.

900
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:08,830
In my eyes...

901
00:32:15,110 --> 00:32:17,370
You're always in the center of the stage.

902
00:32:25,070 --> 00:32:26,070
Take a proper photo of me.

903
00:32:26,070 --> 00:32:26,580
Sure.

904
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:27,600
Come on.

905
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,260
Let's do it.

906
00:32:28,700 --> 00:32:29,320
Careful!

907
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:29,930
I'm fine.

908
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:34,410
Come on, look here.

909
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:36,680
Now, look at the camera.

910
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:39,470
One, two, three.

911
00:32:39,700 --> 00:32:40,160
Smile.

912
00:32:41,340 --> 00:32:42,370
One more photo.

913
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:42,920
Come on.

914
00:32:44,070 --> 00:32:47,400
One, two, three. Smile!

915
00:32:48,420 --> 00:32:48,910
Done.

916
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:56,650
This is nice.

917
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:59,560
How can it be nice,
now that you're injured?

918
00:33:00,150 --> 00:33:02,350
I don't mind getting injured every day.

919
00:33:03,740 --> 00:33:05,000
What's that nonsense?

920
00:33:16,190 --> 00:33:16,990
So beautiful.

921
00:33:37,380 --> 00:33:38,440
Which meal is this?

922
00:33:38,570 --> 00:33:39,460
I just woke up.

923
00:33:41,940 --> 00:33:43,070
Did you drink again?

924
00:33:44,510 --> 00:33:45,110
Mr. Chu

925
00:33:45,140 --> 00:33:46,740
introduced me to a director.

926
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:51,740
What role did you get this time?

927
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:53,700
We didn't get into the details.

928
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:54,980
All we had was dinner.

929
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:56,960
Well...

930
00:33:57,810 --> 00:33:59,510
You always dine with them and get nothing.

931
00:33:59,510 --> 00:34:00,610
God knows what you guys

932
00:34:00,610 --> 00:34:01,940
talk about at the table.

933
00:34:02,770 --> 00:34:03,370
This is...

934
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:05,720
Wait. Are you

935
00:34:05,830 --> 00:34:07,310
silly or what?

936
00:34:07,530 --> 00:34:09,940
Stop nagging me, okay?

937
00:34:10,610 --> 00:34:12,630
My head already hurts like hell.

938
00:34:16,730 --> 00:34:17,820
Are you sure this is proper food?

939
00:34:17,820 --> 00:34:19,080
E-Eat something else.

940
00:34:19,150 --> 00:34:20,440
What are you doing?

941
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:22,570
I've been eating out these past few days.

942
00:34:22,570 --> 00:34:24,900
I just want to have
some home-made cooking.

943
00:34:24,900 --> 00:34:25,480
I'm not sure

944
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:27,429
if what I'm making is any good.

945
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,110
You want home-made cooking? No problem.

946
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,719
Just come eat at my home.

947
00:34:33,610 --> 00:34:35,380
I don't mean anything particular by it.

948
00:34:35,380 --> 00:34:37,880
I would just love for you to try

949
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:39,260
my parents' cooking.

950
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,719
My dad is an amazing cook.

951
00:34:41,170 --> 00:34:43,690
He's good at cooking pork shoulder,
meatballs,

952
00:34:43,690 --> 00:34:45,010
and noodles in soybean paste

953
00:34:45,010 --> 00:34:47,730
with his secret recipes.

954
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,130
You should try them.

955
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:53,290
No,

956
00:34:53,360 --> 00:34:54,860
let me rephrase it.

957
00:34:54,900 --> 00:34:56,830
I just hope to introduce you

958
00:34:56,880 --> 00:34:58,600
to my parents

959
00:34:58,650 --> 00:35:00,230
over dinner,

960
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:01,210
so you can

961
00:35:01,380 --> 00:35:02,960
get to know each other.

962
00:35:04,230 --> 00:35:04,960
Is that okay?

963
00:35:08,690 --> 00:35:10,220
Turn it off and come with me.

964
00:35:11,130 --> 00:35:11,860
Twist it that way.

965
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:12,460
Which way?

966
00:35:12,530 --> 00:35:13,650
To the left.

967
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:14,760
Lili,

968
00:35:15,760 --> 00:35:17,170
you may not trust me,

969
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:19,240
but you do trust my father, right?

970
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:21,860
My dad can arrange

971
00:35:21,860 --> 00:35:23,170
a comfortable job for you.

972
00:35:23,170 --> 00:35:25,070
All it takes is a word from him.

973
00:35:30,420 --> 00:35:31,480
Don't be like this.

974
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:33,840
This is only our second time meeting.

975
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:34,820
We were strangers

976
00:35:34,820 --> 00:35:36,260
the first time, but friends the next time!

977
00:35:36,260 --> 00:35:37,690
Please don't do this.

978
00:35:38,030 --> 00:35:39,090
What are you doing?

979
00:35:42,880 --> 00:35:44,410
The sun hasn't even set yet.

980
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:45,610
What are you doing here,

981
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:46,870
making all that noise?

982
00:35:47,070 --> 00:35:48,200
I heard everything.

983
00:35:48,380 --> 00:35:49,400
The girl is reluctant.

984
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:50,840
You're being a rogue, you know?

985
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:52,160
Who are you?

986
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:53,450
None of your business.

987
00:35:53,980 --> 00:35:55,320
If you have a problem with me,

988
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:57,360
let's go to
the joint security station nearby.

989
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:58,000
We can spend a while there,

990
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:58,400
buddy.

991
00:35:59,530 --> 00:36:00,860
He and I know each other.

992
00:36:01,070 --> 00:36:02,070
You know each other?

993
00:36:02,070 --> 00:36:02,920
We're dating!

994
00:36:04,630 --> 00:36:05,510
Dating?

995
00:36:06,150 --> 00:36:07,210
I don't care if you're dating

996
00:36:07,210 --> 00:36:07,940
or whatever.

997
00:36:08,570 --> 00:36:09,360
What you're doing here

998
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:09,860
in broad daylight

999
00:36:09,860 --> 00:36:11,210
is just not appropriate.

1000
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:11,820
You know?

1001
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:13,780
If you're really dating,

1002
00:36:13,980 --> 00:36:14,590
get intimate at home

1003
00:36:14,590 --> 00:36:15,850
or somewhere private.

1004
00:36:16,110 --> 00:36:17,550
Then you can do anything you want.

1005
00:36:17,550 --> 00:36:19,000
But it's improper to behave like that here

1006
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:20,600
in front of people, isn't it?

1007
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:21,350
Alright.

1008
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:22,150
Today,

1009
00:36:23,030 --> 00:36:24,090
I'll do a good deed.

1010
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:26,770
There's a hostel nearby.

1011
00:36:27,030 --> 00:36:27,820
The cost is low,

1012
00:36:27,820 --> 00:36:28,630
and the service is good.

1013
00:36:28,630 --> 00:36:29,320
You can do whatever

1014
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,130
you want there.

1015
00:36:30,130 --> 00:36:30,760
Isn't it nice?

1016
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:32,630
D-Did anyone ask to go to a hostel?

1017
00:36:33,150 --> 00:36:34,780
I'm not going to a hostel!

1018
00:36:34,900 --> 00:36:35,710
You creep.

1019
00:36:36,340 --> 00:36:36,800
Lili!

1020
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:37,800
Lili!

1021
00:36:38,110 --> 00:36:39,150
Let me take you to dinner!

1022
00:36:39,150 --> 00:36:39,480
Look at that.

1023
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,880
Let's go have roast duck!

1024
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,950
How am I a creep now?

1025
00:36:48,460 --> 00:36:49,000
Sir,

1026
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:51,320
our customers have all been

1027
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:53,360
driven away by that saxophone player.

1028
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:54,070
Is he still coming today?

1029
00:36:54,070 --> 00:36:55,000
Of course he is.

1030
00:36:55,570 --> 00:36:57,110
None of us will have any peace

1031
00:36:57,110 --> 00:36:58,860
until he gets enough of that junk.

1032
00:36:58,860 --> 00:36:59,550
He thinks he plays it

1033
00:36:59,550 --> 00:37:00,170
so well.

1034
00:37:00,170 --> 00:37:00,840
Dad,

1035
00:37:01,460 --> 00:37:02,260
I'm back!

1036
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,140
Will you do me the honor

1037
00:37:07,860 --> 00:37:08,820
of coming with me?

1038
00:37:08,820 --> 00:37:10,680
What stunt are you pulling today?

1039
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:12,340
Don't think I won't beat you up

1040
00:37:12,340 --> 00:37:13,940
just because you're a sweet talker.

1041
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:15,240
Beat me if necessary.

1042
00:37:18,340 --> 00:37:19,200
Come here, Dad.

1043
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:21,800
Hello, Uncle Tao.

1044
00:37:22,590 --> 00:37:23,390
-Hello.
-Dad,

1045
00:37:23,650 --> 00:37:24,710
this is Shen Ranran.

1046
00:37:24,710 --> 00:37:25,170
Ranran,

1047
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:27,000
this is my father.

1048
00:37:30,460 --> 00:37:31,460
A friend of yours?

1049
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:35,960
Have a seat.

1050
00:37:36,030 --> 00:37:37,250
After you, Uncle Tao.

1051
00:37:37,510 --> 00:37:38,780
Do be seated.

1052
00:37:40,130 --> 00:37:41,510
You bought so many things.

1053
00:37:41,510 --> 00:37:43,000
She said she couldn't show up

1054
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:44,600
empty-handed for the visit.

1055
00:37:51,030 --> 00:37:52,000
What do you mean by this?

1056
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:52,800
I'm telling you,

1057
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:53,940
if you mess with me today,

1058
00:37:53,940 --> 00:37:54,900
you won't be able to leave this place,

1059
00:37:54,900 --> 00:37:55,440
you know?

1060
00:37:55,610 --> 00:37:56,360
It's not that, buddy.

1061
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:57,820
I just need a word with you.

1062
00:37:58,110 --> 00:37:59,960
About what? Where's your girlfriend?

1063
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:00,840
She's gone to the bathroom.

1064
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,230
Well...

1065
00:38:01,230 --> 00:38:01,590
I thought

1066
00:38:01,590 --> 00:38:03,010
you two had gone for dinner.

1067
00:38:03,010 --> 00:38:04,510
Are you familiar with the hostel

1068
00:38:04,510 --> 00:38:05,570
you just mentioned?

1069
00:38:05,570 --> 00:38:06,130
Yes.

1070
00:38:06,190 --> 00:38:07,120
I own that place.

1071
00:38:09,300 --> 00:38:11,030
So you were just hustling
for your hostel here?

1072
00:38:11,030 --> 00:38:12,170
How was I hustling for my hostel?

1073
00:38:12,170 --> 00:38:13,650
I did what I did for your own good.

1074
00:38:13,650 --> 00:38:14,530
You would've been taken

1075
00:38:14,530 --> 00:38:15,320
to the police station

1076
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:16,150
if that girl had screamed louder.

1077
00:38:16,150 --> 00:38:17,230
Do you believe that?

1078
00:38:17,230 --> 00:38:18,690
Thank you then. Thank you.

1079
00:38:18,900 --> 00:38:19,420
Now tell me

1080
00:38:19,420 --> 00:38:20,150
where the hotel is.

1081
00:38:20,150 --> 00:38:21,610
I'll meet you there later.

1082
00:38:22,780 --> 00:38:25,090
It's not far from here.
Just turn the corner ahead,

1083
00:38:25,090 --> 00:38:26,220
and enter Luogu Hutong to look for

1084
00:38:26,220 --> 00:38:27,300
the Seasons Change Hostel.

1085
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:28,940
Ask around. People all know it.

1086
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:30,400
Leave the door open for me!

1087
00:38:30,820 --> 00:38:31,360
Listen,

1088
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:32,930
I get off work at 11:00 p.m.!

1089
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,630
-Just be seated.
-I'd like to help.

1090
00:38:35,630 --> 00:38:37,510
Don't bother with that. Let him do it.

1091
00:38:37,510 --> 00:38:38,050
Come on.

1092
00:38:38,110 --> 00:38:39,710
Wash your hands and get ready to eat.

1093
00:38:39,710 --> 00:38:40,900
Help yourself to whatever beverage

1094
00:38:40,900 --> 00:38:42,030
you like over there.

1095
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:42,840
Auntie,

1096
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:44,460
why not let me help you
bring the dishes out?

1097
00:38:44,460 --> 00:38:45,210
No need.

1098
00:38:45,210 --> 00:38:46,900
Just sit back and wait here.

1099
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:48,770
Thanks, auntie.

1100
00:38:49,230 --> 00:38:50,180
Honey!

1101
00:38:50,940 --> 00:38:52,800
Slice the braised pork shoulder.

1102
00:38:53,030 --> 00:38:54,120
Already done.

1103
00:38:54,150 --> 00:38:55,750
I'm making the garlic sauce.

1104
00:38:56,050 --> 00:38:56,730
That girl

1105
00:38:56,730 --> 00:38:58,150
is quite pretty.

1106
00:38:58,210 --> 00:38:59,880
Did our son say
what their relationship is?

1107
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,410
Just friends, aren't they?

1108
00:39:01,780 --> 00:39:02,510
Liangliang!

1109
00:39:03,230 --> 00:39:04,190
Get the dishes out.

1110
00:39:04,190 --> 00:39:04,650
Coming.

1111
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:08,600
Which one?

1112
00:39:10,070 --> 00:39:11,800
She's your girlfriend, right?

1113
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:16,140
Why are you like this?

1114
00:39:16,170 --> 00:39:17,210
And why are you like this?

1115
00:39:17,210 --> 00:39:18,670
You've brought many people home

1116
00:39:18,670 --> 00:39:19,960
since childhood,

1117
00:39:19,980 --> 00:39:21,760
but never a girl.

1118
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:24,540
Tell the truth now.

1119
00:39:25,480 --> 00:39:26,540
Do the two of you...

1120
00:39:27,100 --> 00:39:27,810
like her?

1121
00:39:28,210 --> 00:39:29,490
Why ask us?

1122
00:39:30,110 --> 00:39:31,130
If you like her,

1123
00:39:31,190 --> 00:39:32,470
treat her well.

1124
00:39:32,780 --> 00:39:34,230
Bring her home for dinner when you can.

1125
00:39:34,230 --> 00:39:34,880
That's right.

1126
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:36,340
Anyway, I think she's very pretty.

1127
00:39:36,340 --> 00:39:38,070
I also think she's very pretty.

1128
00:39:38,650 --> 00:39:39,250
Oh, right.

1129
00:39:40,480 --> 00:39:41,690
What's Ranran's zodiac sign?

1130
00:39:41,690 --> 00:39:42,750
Pick a bowl for her.

1131
00:39:43,550 --> 00:39:43,950
Right.

1132
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:45,800
Rat.

1133
00:39:47,190 --> 00:39:48,470
Say it now.

1134
00:39:48,610 --> 00:39:49,150
Rat!

1135
00:39:50,150 --> 00:39:51,130
Go find the right bowl then.

1136
00:39:51,130 --> 00:39:52,280
The three of us shouldn't be

1137
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:52,920
whispering here.

1138
00:39:52,920 --> 00:39:53,670
She's been sitting there for a while.

1139
00:39:53,670 --> 00:39:55,420
How is it appropriate?

1140
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:57,620
Get the dishes out now.

1141
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:00,140
Uncle Tao, Auntie Tao,

1142
00:40:00,510 --> 00:40:01,920
today's dinner...

1143
00:40:02,170 --> 00:40:03,400
is a real feast.

1144
00:40:03,860 --> 00:40:05,230
Just some home-made dishes.

1145
00:40:05,230 --> 00:40:05,820
We were worried

1146
00:40:05,820 --> 00:40:07,420
that you wouldn't like the salty flavor

1147
00:40:07,420 --> 00:40:08,250
in the north.

1148
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:09,280
Right?

1149
00:40:10,170 --> 00:40:12,380
I really love these noodles
in soybean paste.

1150
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:13,960
Liangliang kept telling me

1151
00:40:14,070 --> 00:40:14,690
that his cooking

1152
00:40:14,690 --> 00:40:16,170
was not as good as yours,

1153
00:40:16,210 --> 00:40:17,690
and insisted that I come over for dinner.

1154
00:40:17,690 --> 00:40:18,030
Yes.

1155
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:20,460
I learned it from my mom and dad.

1156
00:40:21,300 --> 00:40:22,070
I mean,

1157
00:40:22,190 --> 00:40:24,790
you two make it
in a more authentic way than I do.

1158
00:40:26,260 --> 00:40:27,610
-Hurry, try the food.
-Come on.

1159
00:40:27,610 --> 00:40:28,710
Come on, dig in.

1160
00:40:29,070 --> 00:40:29,380
Mom,

1161
00:40:29,420 --> 00:40:30,530
-focus on your portion.
-I can do it...

1162
00:40:30,530 --> 00:40:31,790
And I'll focus on mine.

1163
00:40:32,920 --> 00:40:33,360
Fine.

1164
00:40:34,150 --> 00:40:35,350
You have some of this.

1165
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:35,940
Here.

1166
00:40:38,820 --> 00:40:39,650
Ranran,

1167
00:40:40,050 --> 00:40:41,180
how are you adapting

1168
00:40:41,210 --> 00:40:42,900
to the life in a small hostel in the north

1169
00:40:42,900 --> 00:40:44,190
as a girl from the south?

1170
00:40:44,190 --> 00:40:45,210
I'm adapting well.

1171
00:40:45,210 --> 00:40:46,630
Although the place is small,

1172
00:40:46,630 --> 00:40:48,360
we are very happy living there.

1173
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:48,990
Well,

1174
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:51,260
mainly because I'm around, right?

1175
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:56,110
Right. Liangliang takes great care of me.

1176
00:40:56,110 --> 00:40:57,050
That's the right thing to do.

1177
00:40:57,050 --> 00:40:58,320
You young people should take care

1178
00:40:58,320 --> 00:41:00,070
of each other
since you're always together.

1179
00:41:00,070 --> 00:41:03,270
That's the only way to put my mind
and my husband's at ease.

1180
00:41:03,420 --> 00:41:04,900
You have high cholesterol and blood sugar.

1181
00:41:04,900 --> 00:41:06,050
How can you eat this?

1182
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,500
Ranran, have some more.

1183
00:41:09,230 --> 00:41:09,610
Thank you, auntie.

1184
00:41:09,610 --> 00:41:10,510
You look very thin.

1185
00:41:10,510 --> 00:41:11,640
You should eat more.

1186
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:12,530
Try this.

1187
00:41:15,110 --> 00:41:15,480
Dad,

1188
00:41:16,230 --> 00:41:17,690
Mom is actually asking you

1189
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:19,460
to have more lean meat.

1190
00:41:21,070 --> 00:41:22,130
That piece is fine.

1191
00:41:22,630 --> 00:41:23,670
-Delicious!
-How is it?

1192
00:41:23,670 --> 00:41:25,200
I'll stop my diet for today.

1193
00:41:25,860 --> 00:41:26,960
That's the spirit.

1194
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:28,600
Well, this...

1195
00:41:29,210 --> 00:41:31,140
My dad has a secret recipe for this.

1196
00:41:31,190 --> 00:41:31,900
A family recipe

1197
00:41:31,900 --> 00:41:33,230
that he'll pass it to me.

1198
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:36,080
I made it too salty this time.

1199
00:41:36,860 --> 00:41:38,320
I'll pass the recipe to Liangliang,

1200
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:39,650
so he can make it for you.

1201
00:41:41,950 --> 00:41:43,380
How do you know it's too salty?

1202
00:41:43,380 --> 00:41:44,690
You sneaked a bite behind me, didn't you?

1203
00:41:44,690 --> 00:41:46,420
I tasted it to see
if it was properly seasoned.

1204
00:41:46,420 --> 00:41:48,230
Hey, there's much oil in it.

1205
00:41:48,630 --> 00:41:50,170
You just wouldn't listen to me,

1206
00:41:50,170 --> 00:41:50,770
would you?

1207
00:41:52,690 --> 00:41:53,340
Ranran,

1208
00:41:54,260 --> 00:41:56,030
is filming tiring for you?

1209
00:41:56,420 --> 00:41:57,000
I heard

1210
00:41:57,030 --> 00:41:58,070
actresses can't even have

1211
00:41:58,070 --> 00:41:59,270
hot meals. Is it true?

1212
00:41:59,670 --> 00:42:01,030
Mom, let's eat first,

1213
00:42:01,170 --> 00:42:03,570
before the food gets old.
We can talk later.

1214
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,590
W-What's going on?

1215
00:42:08,530 --> 00:42:09,330
Oh, Ranran...

1216
00:42:11,780 --> 00:42:12,710
Anything wrong?

1217
00:42:13,530 --> 00:42:15,730
No, I'm just getting a little homesick.

1218
00:42:17,050 --> 00:42:18,110
I spoke out of turn.

1219
00:42:18,640 --> 00:42:19,520
Don't be upset.

1220
00:42:19,550 --> 00:42:20,570
If you ever feel homesick,

1221
00:42:20,570 --> 00:42:21,530
just come over here.

1222
00:42:21,530 --> 00:42:23,570
My husband
will cook something delicious for you.

1223
00:42:23,570 --> 00:42:24,730
Bring your clothes over too.

1224
00:42:24,730 --> 00:42:25,990
I'll wash them for you.

1225
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:28,950
A girl living away from home

1226
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:30,550
should take good care of herself

1227
00:42:30,550 --> 00:42:31,950
and not worry her family.

1228
00:42:32,340 --> 00:42:32,920
Right?

1229
00:42:33,390 --> 00:42:35,210
Let Ranran eat.

1230
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:36,810
Don't nag her ear off.

1231
00:42:37,920 --> 00:42:39,260
I'm just overjoyed.

1232
00:42:40,260 --> 00:42:41,070
Eat up.

1233
00:42:41,210 --> 00:42:42,510
We'll have plenty of time to talk, right?

1234
00:42:42,510 --> 00:42:44,130
Come on, clink our glasses too.

1235
00:42:44,130 --> 00:42:45,130
Right, together.

1236
00:42:46,110 --> 00:42:46,910
How very nice.

1237
00:42:50,010 --> 00:42:50,560
Ranran,

1238
00:42:50,690 --> 00:42:52,150
try the soy-braised beef.

1239
00:42:54,570 --> 00:42:55,500
Now even I can reach it.
